                     ear;

div.p:
Three miles beyond this River is the out side of Massecusets Patent;
wherein these are the Towns that were begun in the year,
1633.

Their Language is very copious and large,Their Language. and hard to be learned;
And though in an hundred miles distance their Languages differ, yet
not so much, but they can understand each other.

The Cherry Tree is not altogether so large, the fruit is useless and insiped;
The colour some resembling our Cherries, and the shape not
unlike.
